topic.title: Clock Pins

li.p: REFCLK termination is required, please see PCIe Reference Clock Electrical
Connections for REFCLKs are outlined in Clocking Architecture

entry.p: Accepts a low-jitter free-running clock at 100 MHz, used by the serial stream clock recovery logic and synthesis logic for SerDes connected to drive ports.
Accepts a low-jitter 100 MHz PCIe Base Specification compliant reference clock.
This clock is routed to stacks 0, 1, 2 (CSUs 0 and 1)
Accepts a low-jitter 100 MHz PCIe Base Specification compliant reference clock.
This clock is routed to stacks 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 (All CSUs)
Accepts a low-jitter 100 MHz PCIe Base Specification compliant reference clock.
This clock is routed to stacks 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 (All CSUs)
Accepts a low-jitter 100 MHz PCIe Base Specification compliant reference clock.
This clock is routed to stacks 3, 4, 5 (CSUs 2 and 3)
